   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Chronic recurring ($1,000-5,000/yr) | Front-loaded ($5,000-15,000 per treatment episode) |
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Therapist time
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Minimal (15-min med check) | 6-8 hrs per session (bottleneck) |
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key insight:
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The competitive advantage of psychedelics is the 
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: paradigm shift from chronic daily medication to
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: episodic treatment
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,730:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . This fundamentally changes the pharmacoeconomic model — but creates a delivery infrastructure
   DEBUG: 2026-06-17 16:40:35,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: challenge (trained therapists, supervised clinical settings).
